                        <objectDesc>
                            <supportDesc>
                                <support>
                                    <p>The monument on which the inscription is placed is a slab of local limestone decorated with bas-relief and figures in the round. 
                                        The representation on the front face is obtained by the superimposition of a circular shield, a groom's left leg seen in profile and 
                                        a horse moving towards the left. The monument is carved on three sides, measuring 125 cm wide, 70 cm high and 70 cm deep.</p>
                                    <material ana="#material.stone.limestone" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/66.html">limestone</material>
                                    <objectType ana="#object.funerary_monument" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/230.html">funerary monument</objectType>
